post_text: Thank you so much Tim and Andrea Brady!!
shared_text:
Meade School District
June 3 at 9:47 AM ·

Meade School District is pleased to announce that a generous donation has been received to pay off all student lunch balances at Piedmont Elementary School and Stagebarn Middle School.

A check in the amount of $2337.98 was received from Tim and Andrea Brady of Kumelos Design and Construction, Inc. of Piedmont, SD.

The donation paid off the lunch balances of 53 students in the Piedmont and Summerset areas, giving those families a fresh start for the coming school year.

Thank you so much, Bradys! You are school lunch heroes!

Make sure you mention that you want to support PVE PTA.

There will be some major changes in how we host this year's program, including the addition of more showings, assigned showtime/dates that you choose, assigned seating that you choose, and limiting the amount of punch cards available per day/showtime.

Have some questions? Please call us at 343-7888.

School Food Deliveries for the Easter Holiday will be as follows:

There will be no distribution on Good Friday, April 10.
Distribution for the following week will be on Tuesday, April 14th and Thursday, April 16th. Children will receive two days worth of Breakfasts and Lunches on each of those days.

Please see the Meade School District Facebook Page for details about curbside pickup and bus delivery sites, or call the foodservice office at 605-347-3601.

post_text:
The Teacher/Staff Wave Parade is coming!!

We will be doing 2 wave parades!! Each parade will start at 2pm. We ask that everyone stays out of the roads. Please stay on the sidewalks and grass! Feel free to make a signs, banners and cheer for the staff as they make their rounds.

Tuesday March 31st will start at PVE and will be Piedmont, Stagebarn Development, and Sun Valley.

Wednesday April 1st will start at Stagebarn Middle School and will go by Bright Beginnings and Challenging Minds, Wonderland Homes, and Summerset.

Please not because of how big our area please note we can not cover every neighborhood.

Sites will operate with all deliveries and pickups happening only on Monday, Wednesday, and Friday. Children will receive two sets of meals on Monday and Wednesday. See our FB page for more details.

post_text: Meade Schools will be providing free meals for enrolled students beginning Monday, March 23rd. Meals will be made at Stagebarn Middle School and Sturgis Elementary School by foodservice staff. Each child will receive a full lunch and breakfast each school day. Curbside pickup will be available 11:00 am to Noon at Stagebarn Middle School and Sturgis Elementary, and lunches will also be delivered to Piedmont Valley Elementary and Whitewood elementary for distribution. Lunches will be free for all enrolled students, but students must be present at pick-up or drop-off and school employees will need to check off their name. Some delivery routes are being planned to reach neighborhoods where children may not have transportation to the pick-up sites. If you would like to request delivery to your neighborhood, please call the foodservice office at 605-347-3601 and leave a message.

post_text:
If you have not heard yet, our beloved principal, Ethan Dschaak, has had a minor setback in his cancer recovery. The doctors at Mayo Clinic have found what they believe is a cancerous tumor on his left lung. He will be undergoing surgery very soon to have it removed. To show our support we have created shirts to show our support. Your child will be sent home with an order form this week so that you can order shirts.

Order’s are due by February 18th, 2020. When sending in orders please include the Child’s name and their Classroom Teacher. We will accept Cash or Checks (with checks made out to PVE PTA).

Please note all sales are final-No refunds or Exchanges
